article.description: Paige Fiedorowicz scored nine of her 15 points in the second half to help Marquette beat No. 23 Wisconsin-Green 63-60 Sunday.
article.headline: Marquette holds on to hand No. 17 Wisconsin-Green Bay its first loss
article.linkText: Marquette first to beat No. 17 Wisc.-Green Bay
article.story:
MILWAUKEE --  Paige Fiedorowicz scored nine of her 15 points in the second half to help Marquette beat Wisconsin-Green (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) 63-60 Sunday.

Kayla Tetschlag's 17 points led Green Bay (9-1), which had its 17-game regular season winning streak snapped.

Green Bay, which never led, got to within two on Sarah Eichler's driving basket with 14.1 seconds to go, but Sarina Simmons sank one of two free throws for the final margin.

A desperation 3 by Adrian Ritchie fell short as Marquette (8-2) beat Green Bay for the first time in the past three meetings.
